name: Sakhalin Leaf Warbler
rangeDescription: Sakhalin, kuril islands, and hokkaido (northern japan)
description: Small songbird, virtually identical in plumage to Pale-legged Leaf Warbler, of which it was formerly considered a subspecies. Vertical tail pumping distinguishes this species from most others in its range except Pale-legged.

name: Harwood's Spurfowl
description: A dark, medium-sized francolin with a large patch of red bare skin around the eyes, and a red bill and legs. The blackish feathers of the back, neck, and underparts have pale fringes.

name: Palawan Babbler
description: A medium-sized bird of lowland forest tangles and bamboo on Palawan and Balabac. Medium-brown above with more rufous on the tail, shoulder, and forecrown.

name: Plumbeous Euphonia
rangeDescription: Southern venezuela to guyana, suriname, and northern amazonian brazil
description: A small mosly gray finch with a yellow belly and contrasting pale bluish bill. Rather uncommon and generally restricted to scrub habitats and taller secondary forests on weathered, sandy soils.

name: Pacific Loon
rangeDescription: Coastal eastern siberia and northern north america; winters to japan and southern baja california
description: A medium-sized loon, common in western North America and across the Pacific to Japan. Dark overall and relatively short-billed for a loon, with a rounded crown and nape.
